{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ECfGza7NPhpzSJ8fERKuwu","type":"tool_result","content":"   120→/-- Outer product: v ⊗ k^T -/\n   121→def outerProduct {m n : ℕ} (v : Fin m → ℝ) (k : Fin n → ℝ) :\n   122→    Matrix (Fin m) (Fin n) ℝ :=\n   123→  Matrix.of fun i j => v i * k j\n   124→\n   125→/-- Single-head E88 state update: S' = tanh(α·S + δ·(v ⊗ k^T))\n   126→    This is the core E88 recurrence that creates nonlinear temporal dynamics. -/\n   127→noncomputable def e88HeadUpdate (head : E88Head d d) (state : HeadState d)\n   128→    (input : Fin d → ℝ) : HeadState d :=\n   129→  let k := head.keyProj.mulVec input\n   130→  let v := head.valueProj.mulVec input\n   131→  let preActivation := head.α • state + head.δ • outerProduct v k\n   132→  matrixTanh preActivation\n   133→\n   134→/-- E88 state after T timesteps for a single head -/\n   135→noncomputable def e88HeadStateAfterT (head : E88Head d d) (T : ℕ)\n   136→    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) (initState : HeadState d := 0) : HeadState d :=\n   137→  List.foldl (fun s x => e88HeadUpdate head s x) initState (List.ofFn inputs)\n   138→\n   139→/-- Multi-head E88 state evolution.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"23a5d44b-efaf-4468-b1ae-0b067e647cf0","uuid":"a38e74c4-23a6-4208-bdb2-c946a0aefe99","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/erikg/elman-proofs/ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E88Definition.lean","content":"/-- Outer product: v ⊗ k^T -/\ndef outerProduct {m n : ℕ} (v : Fin m → ℝ) (k : Fin n → ℝ) :\n    Matrix (Fin m) (Fin n) ℝ :=\n  Matrix.of fun i j => v i * k j\n\n/-- Single-head E88 state update: S' = tanh(α·S + δ·(v ⊗ k^T))\n    This is the core E88 recurrence that creates nonlinear temporal dynamics. -/\nnoncomputable def e88HeadUpdate (head : E88Head d d) (state : HeadState d)\n    (input : Fin d → ℝ) : HeadState d :=\n  let k := head.keyProj.mulVec input\n  let v := head.valueProj.mulVec input\n  let preActivation := head.α • state + head.δ • outerProduct v k\n  matrixTanh preActivation\n\n/-- E88 state after T timesteps for a single head -/\nnoncomputable def e88HeadStateAfterT (head : E88Head d d) (T : ℕ)\n    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) (initState : HeadState d := 0) : HeadState d :=\n  List.foldl (fun s x => e88HeadUpdate head s x) initState (List.ofFn inputs)\n\n/-- Multi-head E88 state evolution.","numLines":20,"startLine":120,"totalLines":651}}}
