ation claim, line 45 in E88RankAccumulation.lean is just a comment, so I need to point to the actual theorems instead: either `e88_achieves_full_rank` at line 161 or `e88_temporal_capacity` at line 173 would be more appropriate. The documentation describes how rank-1 updates accumulate to T × 2d degrees of freedom, and with tanh nonlinearity mixing information across the matrix entries, full rank becomes achievable for T ≥ d.\n\nThe linear recurrence comparison at line 120 aligns with `linear_update_rank_bounded` at line 114, which establishes that linear systems have fundamentally different rank growth constraints. For the tanh saturation property, `tanh_derivative_vanishes` correctly captures how the derivative approaches zero as the function saturates. Now checking the attention persistence claim...\n\nThe nonzero fixed point theorem at line 212 properly establishes that when alpha exceeds 1, the zero fixed point destabilizes and two symmetric stable points emerge satisfying the self-consistency equation. I'm also verifying the latching versus decay comparison at line 360, which examines how linear recurrences with damping factors less than 1 exhibit exponential decay over time. I've finished reviewing those specific lines and now I need to check a few more locations across the codebase—looking at TanhSaturation.lean around line 320 and 424, then moving through the remaining files to verify their documentation accuracy.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2870,"cache_read_input_tokens":46642,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2870},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"23a5d44b-efaf-4468-b1ae-0b067e647cf0","uuid":"62c306ea-55f4-4b34-818a-6f7e51852cc7"}
